name: Spice Goa

reviews.review_text: In a quest to search for the best Goan fish thali, we landed here on a weekend during lunch hours and oh boy, it was a painful wait of an hour in the scorching heat. Even after we had booked a table for 8 the previous night through Easy Diner platform, the restaurant denied and did not honour our booking because of an issue between them and the Easy Diner platform. We were seated on the top deck after an hour and we ordered a few Fish Thalis, King Fish masala fry, egg fried rice, chicken lollipops, Goan veg platter and veg biryani and a few drinks to go with it. As soon as the thali arrived, we started belting and collectively decided that this was the best Goan Fish thali out of all the thalis we had during our 6-day trip to Goa. The prawns curry, the boneless fish fry, the sides to go with it were all very tasty and fulfilling. Even the barfi on the plate was too good. Chicken lollipops and egg fried rice were great too. King Fish masala fry was a bit sour to our taste and was not liked by everyone. The server did give us a heads up about it before we ordered it, so it's all good. The only disappointment was the Goan veg platter. Paying a premium for such less veg sides was not a good plan and the items did not taste very well either. Overall, it was a great experience devouring Goan fish thali and other seafood and chicken items here. A worthy visit and I highly recommend this place for other tourists/travellers. The restrooms were neat and clean and the sinks were kept well and tidy too. The restaurant has won a lot of awards and accolades and the same has been stuck on the wall and one can witness it while going to the top deck. The only nitpicking here i would do is the cramped space and how tiny the restaurant and the waiting area is. It is a very cramped space and a 6 feet human has to bend and watch their head on the top deck while walking around. Even the crowd gets too busy and takes away the ambience of having good food. The waiting area is overfilled during peak lunch hours and one has to stay back in the heat while their family and/or friends wait in the car with the comfort of air conditioning until they get a table confirmation.

Great food, Service and atmosphere is good too.
You can try goan food and north Indian as well.

Overhyped restaurant. The cramped & noisy ambience is a telltale of the obnoxious & rude service being provided by the outlet. We found no tissues on the table,no water was offered,no finger bowls & a general apathy towards customers. The food at best was decent. Nothing to match the hype. Plenty of brilliant restaurants in Goa. Makes no sense visiting this restaurant. Not recommended.

description:
### Spice Goa: A Culinary Gem in the Heart of Goa

With an impressive rating of **4.4 stars** from over **5,300 reviews**, **Spice Goa** stands as a beloved dining destination for locals and tourists alike. This restaurant is particularly renowned for its **Goan specialties**, including the much-lauded **fish thali** and a variety of **seafood** dishes. A glimpse into the customer feedback reveals a frequent mention of delightful elements such as **serradura** (a traditional Goan dessert), meals served on **banana leaves**, and the overall vibrant offerings that encapsulate the essence of Goan cuisine.

### Ambiance & Design

As guests approach Spice Goa, they are greeted by a lively atmosphere that reflects the bustling spirit of Goa. The restaurant features both indoor seating and a more open top deck, which, though charming, does come with constraints‚Äîexpectations of cramped spaces, particularly during peak hours, as noted in various reviews. Warm lighting coupled with colorful d√©cor gives Spice Goa an inviting yet busy ambiance. Guests may find themselves squeezed in during busy lunch hours, with the crowded conditions potentially stealing away from the dining experience. Nevertheless, notable accolades plastered on the walls pay homage to the restaurant‚Äôs reputation and success‚Äîa pleasing sight while climbing to the top deck.

### Menu & Culinary Experience

The culinary offerings at Spice Goa are where the establishment truly shines. Diners rave about the **Goan fish thali**, noted as one of the best during their explorations of Goa‚Äîhighlighting succulent **prawns curry**, perfectly fried **boneless fish**, and flavorsome **sides**. The presentation of dishes is as stunning as it is tempting, with vibrant colors and thoughtful arrangements creating a feast for the eyes as well. For those seeking variety, the menu also includes **North Indian** options, **chicken lollipops**, and a Goan vegetarian platter, although reviews indicate that the veg platter may not meet expectations. Specialty drinks, including various **shakes**, enhance the experience, making it even more enjoyable. On the dessert front, the **serradura** comes highly recommended, adding a sweet finish to a delectable meal.

### Customer Experience & Service

Customer experiences at Spice Goa are decidedly mixed. While many have applauded the friendly service and knowledge of the staff‚Äîwho offer recommendations and insights on menu items‚Äîother patrons have expressed frustration with service deficiencies, including delays and overlooked basics such as providing tissues or water. Despite pre-booking through platforms like Easy Diner, a few customers reported issues with honoring reservations, leading to long waits in the sun. The restaurant‚Äôs policies lean towards a casual dining experience, but the inconsistency in service can overshadow the culinary delights for some.

### Popularity & Reviews

The buzz surrounding Spice Goa is palpable, with patrons highlighting both the delicious food and the vibrant atmosphere. Social media buzz suggests a compelling narrative around the restaurant, with many eager diners sharing their experiences. However, the restaurant is at risk of being overhyped, as some reviews caution against expectations possibly not matching the realities of the dining space itself, where noise and crowdedness can detract from the experience. Critics have noted the competitive landscape of Goan restaurants, suggesting that there are plenty of worthy alternatives out there.

### Utilizing Visual Content

The ambiance, food presentation, and overall experiences are beautifully captured in several customer photos. One picture showcases an exquisite spread of colorful fish thali, illustrating the freshness and artistry behind each dish. Other images reflect the vibrant atmosphere of the restaurant, depicting diners enjoying their meals despite the bustling environment. These visuals reinforce the reviews‚Äô sentiments, highlighting both the allure and challenges of Spice Goa's dining experience.

In conclusion, **Spice Goa** offers a tantalizing glimpse into Goan culinary traditions, making it a noteworthy stop for food enthusiasts. While the restaurant excels in its offerings of flavorful dishes served with a side of authentic Goan hospitality, potential visitors should brace themselves for a vibrant, albeit sometimes chaotic dining atmosphere.
